Lonotis animalibus] According to Herodotus the inhabitants of the Theban nome abstained from eating sheep, though they ate goats, while the opposite practice prevailed at Mendes (in the Delta), where they ate sheep and abstained from goats. The cannibalism imputed to the Egyptians is fabulous, though Diodorus says that on the otca- sion of a great famine human flesh was eaten (see verse 93, squ).
